         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>A letter (<t:foreign xml:lang="la">prosphoneticus</t:foreign> ) by <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3255CyrilI">Cyril I</t:persName> addressed to Princesses Arcadia and Marina, sisters of
                  <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9480Theodosi"> Theodosius II </t:persName>. The letter, originally composed in Greek
               according to <t:bibl type="CPG" corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/4TZ6V4PR"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:CPG3"/><title level="m">Clavis patrum Graecorum, III: A Cyrillo Alexandrino ad Iohannem Damascenum</title><title type="short">CPG</title><title level="s">Corpus Christianorum</title><author><forename>Maurice</forename><surname>Geerard</surname></author><pubPlace>Turnhout</pubPlace><publisher>Brepols</publisher><date>1979</date><series><title level="s">Corpus Christianorum</title></series><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:CPG3</note></note><note type="tag">bm:CPG3</note></t:bibl>discusses the nature of Christ, aiming to limit the influence of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7553Nestoriu">Nestorius</t:persName>. Its Gǝʿǝz version is transmitted as part of <t:title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3309Qerellos"> collection.</t:title>
            </t:p>
         </t:abstract>
